title: Parliament unites to honour Bondi massacre victims | 7NEWS
description: Federal Parliament observed a moment of silence to honour the victims of the Bondi massacre, with MPs brought to tears as families of the 15 victims watched from the gallery. Prime Minister Anthony Albanese is negotiating with Opposition Leader Sussan Ley to pass new hate speech and gun control laws in response to the tragedy. A Newspoll shows One Nation has overtaken the Coalition for the first time, becoming Australia's second most popular political party at 22 per cent, with Labor leading at 32 per cent. title: Three shark attacks strike Sydney in two days | 7NEWS
description: Three shark attacks have occurred in Sydney waters within 48 hours. An unconscious surfer was rescued at Manly Beach after a shark mauling and received emergency first aid from bystanders. An 11-year-old was attacked by a suspected bull shark at Dee Why, and 12-year-old Nico Antic remains in critical condition following a separate attack in Sydney Harbour. title: Anti-Semitism laws pass as gun reforms stall | 7NEWS
description: The Australian Parliament is set to pass anti-Semitism legislation after Opposition Leader Susan Lee agreed to a deal, with families of the Bondi terror attack present during proceedings. A separate gun control bill is expected to pass with Greens support, while Queensland has withdrawn from a national gun buyback scheme, joining the Northern Territory and Tasmania in opposing the joint funding arrangement. The federal government's firearm reform efforts face significant challenges as states reject the 50-50 buyback framework. title: Spain train disaster kills 39 in collision | 7NEWS
description: A train disaster in Spain has claimed at least 39 lives after a Madrid-bound train derailed and collided with an oncoming train on opposite tracks, leaving authorities baffled by the incident. Russian President Vladimir Putin has received an invitation from Donald Trump to join a proposed Board of Peace for Gaza. An Airbus A321 aircraft made an emergency landing at Orlando International Airport in severe wind conditions, with the nose wheel detaching upon impact, though no injuries were reported. title: Trump links Nobel snub to Greenland takeover push | 7NEWS
description: U.S. President Donald Trump has sent a text to the Norwegian Prime Minister stating he no longer feels obliged to think purely of peace after not receiving the Nobel Peace Prize, linking this to his push for U.S. control of Greenland. Trump has threatened eight countries, including Norway, with tariffs if they don't accept a U.S. takeover of Greenland, prompting an extraordinary meeting of the 27 European Union nations. The EU is reportedly considering retaliatory trade strikes on U.S. goods and services, which could trigger a global trade meltdown. title: Body found on K'Gari surrounded by dingoes
description: A 19-year-old Canadian tourist has been found dead on K'Gari in Queensland. Police are yet to determine if she drowned or was attacked by dingoes. #kgari #dingo #queensland #police #qldpolice

title: 'We have not seen this before': Shark crisis shuts down Sydney's Northern Beaches | 7NEWS
description: Three shark attacks in 24 hours across Sydney have prompted authorities to close all Northern Beaches for 48 hours. A 27-year-old surfer from Wollongong is in critical condition after being attacked at North Steyne Beach, while a 13-year-old boy remains critical following the Vaucluse attack. Bull sharks are believed responsible, with officials citing turbid water conditions from recent rainfall as creating prime conditions for shark activity. description: A state of catastrophe has been declared in Chile as forest fires ravage large parts of the country. #chile #fire #forestfire #bushfire #southamerica

title: Closure of Eraring power station delayed until 2029
description: The closure of Australia's largest coal plant will be delayed by two years, with the NSW government and Origin Energy announcing Eraring power station near Newcastle will continue to run until 2029. The extension comes following warnings the electricity grid is not prepared for its closure. #eraring #coal #power #environment #nswpol
